# GraphQL Explorer — environment configuration
#
# VITE_GRAPHQL_URL is the SINGLE knob that points the app at the LMDB2GraphQL lens.
# It is REQUIRED — there is no hardcoded default. The app resolves it in exactly one
# place (src/transport/config.ts) and throws loudly at startup if it is unset/blank.
# /ready and /health are derived from the same origin. Copy this file to `.env` and
# set the value to your lens endpoint.
#
# SECURITY (V14): the lens is an UNAUTHENTICATED, full-introspection, wildcard-CORS,
# read-only API. v1 is local-dev only — point this ONLY at a trusted lens. Overriding
# it to a public/untrusted host means the app sends queries to, and trusts responses
# from, that origin. Any wider exposure needs a gateway (auth/rate-limit/TLS) — out of scope.
VITE_GRAPHQL_URL=http://<lens-host>:8080/graphql
